# JABS

Just automating boring stuff

## Usage

To try stuff out, simply:

- cd ~/dev/   # or whereever
- python3 -m venv venv
- git clone https://github.com/hertogp/jabs.git
- pip install < requirements.txt

after which the repo should've been duplicated locally.
You can now use the scripts.  See sections below.


## namedrop

A basic script to add columns to a log.csv file, using ip addresses
and/or prefixes to lookup stuff in other files.  For example:

file: hosts.csv
ip,name,other
1.1.1.1,h_one,internet
10.10.10.10,h_10,local


file: subnets.csv
subnet,name,vpn
1.0.0.0/8,Internet,n/a
10.0.0.0/8,rfc1918,my_org


file: logs.csv
src,dst,proto
10.10.10.1,1.1.1.1,80
10.10.10.10,1.1.1.1,80

then:

cd examples
../namedrop logs.csv -t a:ip:hosts.csv -t b:subnet:subnets.csv -a src:a:name -a src:a:other -a src:b:name -a dst:b:vpn

yields:

src,src_name,src_other,src_name,dst,dst_vpn,proto
10.10.10.1,no_info,no_info,rfc1918,1.1.1.1,n/a,80
10.10.10.10,h_10,local,rfc1918,1.1.1.1,n/a,80

where:
- src_name = hosts.csv{src} -> name
- src_other = hosts.csv{src} -> other
- 2nd src_name = subnets.csv{src} -> name
- dst_vpn = subnets.csv{dst} -> vpn

